review_blob: Aroma of malt, roasted nuts and cola. Medium bitter taste, with toasted notes. Pretty oh-kay.

Cloudy orange beer, with a quickly diminishing white head. Aroma is bubblegum, red currant, lemon juice and roasted almonds. Taste is medium bitter, tart, slightly nutty, very yeasty and malty throughout. Alcohol is well hidden. Rather thin and dry-ish mouthfeel. Not really my kind of beer, but well executed for the style I guess?
Grassy and buttery aroma. Grassy hops, medium bitter taste, kinda weak on the palate.

Blassgelbes Bier mit weisser Schaumkrone. Riecht nach Brot und Nssen. Sehr wssrige Konsistenz aufgrund des geringen Anteils an Kohlensure. Schwach malziger Geschmack, leicht metallische Note im Abgang. Eher langweilig.
Pretty bland malt aroma. Taste is toasted malts, some hops. Full, creamy mouthfeel. Pretty ok.

Yayyy, my first beer from Sweden. Amber beer with a medium sized, off-white head. Aroma of that cactus juice you can get from the supermarket, saffron and CO2. Herbal, tea-like bitterness upfront, that lasts. Not much more going on, maybe a hint of citrus if you want it to be there. More of an english style IPA, quite tasty overall.
beer_name: Brutal Brewing A Ship Full Of IPA

review_blob: Toast and yeast aroma. Medium bitter taste with hints of roasted malt. Bready aftertaste. Quite lively carbonation, medium body.

Slightly cloudy golden beer, with a sizeable white head. Bready and slightly sourish (horseradish?) aroma. Very malty, caramelly taste, not much more going on, maybe a slight fruitiness in the finish.
Drank it straight from the can, so cant say much about appearance. Dark fruit and caramel aroma. Very sweet, slightly toasted taste.
Can. Lemonade and baking powder aroma. Moderate bitterness, wheat, moderate citrus, gentle hop finish.
Fruity esters on the nose; berries, honey, apples. Weak bitterness, solid malt backbone, cereal aftertaste. Medium to heavy body, slightly dry.
Bought as Klausui IPA in Vilnius. Nice tropical fruit and pepper aroma. Decent bitter taste, fruity and biscuit-y finish balances the beer out.
Malty and bready aroma. Fairly malty taste, medium bitterness, lingering pepper burn in the aftertaste.
Prune, raisin and liquor aroma. Taste is a clean bitterness early on, then caramel. Caramel aftertaste. Low carb, fairly light body.
Unimpressive grain aroma. Fairly fruity taste mixed with a sharp tea-like bitterness.
Pretty nice fruity aroma, raisins and candice. Metallic bitterness, light sourness, some caramel.

Light citrus and wheat aroma. Taste is fairly bready and sourish, then has this caramel, almost candylike sweetness going on. Aftertaste of fresh bread. Body is light and heavy at the same time, Im not quite sure how to phrase this correctly, never really encountered such a mix, but the rater before me explained it quite well I think. An unusual, but very tasty, beer made from rye and wheat.
Aroma is mostly grains. Fairly milky malty taste, gentle hops in the finish. Nothing extraordinary about this one.
Weak, malty aroma. Mellow bitterness in the taste, butter. Okay, drinkable, not much more.
Bottle. Aroma is grains, caramel, peach and apples. Taste is medium sweet, weak fruits, no bitterness to speak of. Not really a Pilsner, but in itself a decent beer!

58 cents for a can is a pretty nice price. Bleak corn aroma. Cheap malt ectract and hop pellet taste, watery and slightly dry (or rather dusty) on the palate, quite typical for cheap brews like this. Just bad.

Looks like apple juice, basically. Sightly hazy amber colour with a basically non-existent head. Aroma of white wine, horseradish,  caramelised sugar and of that sour candy spray I used to like as a kid that was supposed to color your tongue green and taste like sour apples. Upfront sourness, then a strong alcoholic note. Sour aftertaste. No sweetness, no bitterness. No dryness, smooth and rather weak body with a fizzy carbonation.

Black body, brown head. Aroma is instant coffee, dessert chocolate, maybe a faint hint of vanilla if you know its supposed to be there. Fairly average stout aroma. Taste is medium bitter, roasty, malty, while a chili spicness (or rather burn) lingers. Creamy texture, heavy body.
Can. Fairly weak malty caramel aroma. Taste is weak bitter, malt extract and a slightly metallic note. Pretty dull and uneventful, but not offensive.
Drank straight from the can. Banana and vanilla aroma. Taste is fruity, medium bitter, banana, medium sour, corn. Kinda weak on the palate. Honestly not bad.
Drank straight from the can. Decent malty and grassy aroma actually, not much worse than that of an honest Pils. Taste is mostly corn, cardboard and malt.
This beer has a nice fruity and yeasty aroma, the taste is kinda watery though, with only faint yeasty and hoppy notes, despite the high carbonation.
Not the strongest aroma of spices and resin. Kinda unimpressive, malty start, then a little bitterness in the finish. Bland and just lacking the bitterness I look for in an IPA.

Bottle, bb 02.07.2016. Clear golden beer with a minimal white head. Weak grainy and grassy aroma. Stingy metallic taste, malts, grain. Fairly high carbonation. Surprisingly bad. An imported craft beer ale, that is worse than the macro lager from the supermarket around the corner... next one, please.

Leicht trbes, hellgelbes Bier mit weisser Schaumkrone. Riecht fruchtig und s, nach Zitrusfrchten, sauren pfeln und Kuchen. Der Geschmack ist vor allem fruchtig, leichte Bananen- und Limonennoten dominieren hier, eine leichte Hopfenbittere bleibt dennoch im Nachgeschmack. Hefig. Eine leckere Wessi-Adaptation des Gose.
Malt and grain aroma. Grassy, weak taste. Cardboard finish. Disappointing...
Biscuity and grainy aroma. Malts and oat in the taste, rather full mouthfeel. Okay.
Bready and grassy aroma of mediocre intensity. Weak bitter taste, light citric and grassy notes. Not a bitter...
Cherry and caramel aroma. Sweet, sugar syrup flavour, without much cherry taste. Gentle bitterness in the aftertaste.
Golden body with a slight haze, white head. Herbal, fruity and piney aroma of medium intensity. Medium bitter, herbal taste, finishes malty. All in all a decent, honest IPA.
Grainy aroma. Fairly mellow taste, with grains and a little malts again. Rather full body, sparkly carbonation. More of a bad pale lager, than a Pils.
Apples, caramel on the nose. Medium bitterness, medium caramel sweetness, fruity notes.
Malty nose with fruity, floral and gummibear aromas. Taste is strangely artificial; alcoholic despite the beer not even being that high in abv., grainy and quite cardboard-like. Not good.
Aroma is more malty than grainy, with some fruity notes. Rather malty taste, notes of corn and nuts, mellow bitterness, some spice.

Pours a hazy, deep purple body, with a pink, albeit quickly diminishing, small head. Aroma of horseradish, fresh carrots, blackcurrant and lemonade. Didnt expect such an aroma, but its complex and pleasant enough. Upfront sourness, almost no fruitiness. Fizzy carbonation.
Aroma is grains and moderate citrus. Bitter-sweet taste, malty and fruity finish. Full body, lower than average carbonation. Nice one.
Hazy gold body, white head. Floral and yeasty aroma. Gentle hop bitterness mixed with fruity and doughy notes.
Dark amber body, minimal off-white head. Toasted almonds, dark fruit and malts on the nose. Taste is medium bitter, roasted, notes of dark chocolate, sour aftertaste.
Clear amber body, lasting white head. Malts, hay and moderate citrus on the nose. Quite strong, resinous bitterness in the taste, sourish, citric aftertaste. Full bodied and dry on the palate.
Quite typical nose for the style, with fruits and clove. Taste is more sweet than sour, with interesting notes of nuts, particularly hazelnuts, in the aftertaste.

Golden beer with a slight haze and a white head. Aroma is grains and butter. Taste has a gentle sourness and some wheat-like sweetness. Grainy taste throughout, especially in the aftertaste. The sourness nicely accentuates the taste of the grain, "orkisz". Creamy body, low carbonation. Pleasant, special taste, reminds me of porridge and cereals.
UPDATED: DEC 24, 2015
Can. Mellow, malty beer, very gentle; an average macro brew in about every aspect. Nice if cold.
Erdbeersyruparoma. Slich, mit eher schwachen Hopfennoten und einer leichten Suerlichkeit. Keine wirkliichen Raucharomen.
beer_name: Browar w Grodzisku Wielkopolskim Piwo naturalne o smaku czerwonej porzeczki

review_blob: Slightly hazy amber beer with a sizeable head. Aroma is faint citrus and hops. Decent bitterness at first, which then gets dry and herbal and leaves a herbal aftertaste behind. Kinda watery on the palate.
